A giant vibrant orange carrot and a weathered wooden stick balanced on opposite ends of an old brass scale, set against a warm sepia-toned background with soft vignette edges. The carrot appears fresh and luminous, almost glowing with appeal, while the stick looks rough and unappealing. Between them, slightly elevated and tipping the scale dramatically in its favor, sits a gleaming vintage smartphone rendered in art deco style with copper and bronze accents. The scene is composed like a 1920s advertisement illustration, with rich textures, grain effects, and muted earth tones punctuated by the carrot's warm orange glow. Decorative flourishes frame the corners in classic vintage poster fashion.
